===Etymology 1===
Old English [[wæx]], from Germanic ''*waxsan'', from Indo-European ''*u̯okso-''.  Cognate with Dutch [[was]], German [[Wachs]], Norwegian [[voks]]; and with Lithuanian [[vaškas]], Russian [[воск]].

